Fuzzy Open (Gedit Plugin)

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS

Downloaded:
1) Extract contents of archive
2a) Copy files from gedit-snapopen directory to
    ~/.gnome2/gedit/plugins
2b) Or install system-wide, copy files to
    /usr/lib/gedit-2/plugins (Ubuntu)
3) Fire up gedit, go to Edit->Preferences, select the
   Plugins tab, and make sure "Fuzzy Open" is checked

GIT clone
1) git clone git://github.com/eggegg/fuzzyopen.git
2a) create a symlink:
      mkdir -p ~/.gnome2/gedit/
      cd ~/.gnome2/gedit/
      ln -s [path/to/clone] plugins
2b) install system wide:
      sudo ln -s [path/to/clone]/fuzzyopen.gedit-plugin /usr/lib/gedit-2/plugins
      sudo ln -s [path/to/clone]/fuzzyopen /usr/lib/gedit-2/plugins

